 Theme: Startup Office IT Setup 
Section A: Scenario-Based Concept Application

1.	Explain the selection process for CPU, RAM, and storage specifications to ensure hardware compatibility and prevent performance bottlenecks for a startup team performing concurrent development and video conferencing tasks.
A) Select multi-core CPU (e.g., Ryzen 5/Intel i5 or better) with high clock speed for concurrent dev + video calls. Choose 16–32GB RAM (DDR4/DDR5) to handle multitasking without swapping. Use NVMe SSD (minimum 512GB) for fast boot/storage. Ensure compatibility to avoid bottlenecks.

2.	Explain how system resource allocation and hardware bottlenecks contribute to performance degradation after the deployment of resource-intensive background applications like antivirus software.
A) Antivirus and background apps consume CPU/RAM/Disk I/O. Poor allocation leads to high utilization → thermal throttling, paging to diskg. This causes lag, freezes, and overall degradation as resources are starved from foreground tasks.

3.	Explain the systematic troubleshooting process for resolving peripheral hardware failures caused by driver incompatibility or operating system conflicts when a device functions inconsistently across different workstations.
A)
•	Check Device Manager for errors/yellow marks. 
•	Update/reinstall drivers from manufacturer site. 
•	Test device on another workstation. 
•	Boot in Safe Mode to isolate OS conflicts. 
•	Check Event Viewer logs and BIOS/UEFI settings. 
•	Replace cable/port if needed.


4.	Explain the role of Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) systems and surge protection in preventing file system corruption and ensuring data integrity during unexpected power fluctuations.
A) UPS(Uninterruptible Power Supply) provides battery backup during outages, allowing safe shutdown and preventing abrupt power loss that corrupts file systems. Surge protectors absorb voltage spikes that can damage components or cause data corruption.

Section B: Practical Application

Task 1: Physically assemble a workstation and document the component installation sequence.
•	Prepare all components(CPU motherboard, RAM, GPU, storage , PSU , cooler, cables).
•	Attach the motherboard and then connect components like RAM, CPU, PCI slots.
